---
import '../styles/home.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>NestForge Docs</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Documentation for building applications with NestForge and contributing to the framework itself."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body class="home-body">
    <header class="home-header">
      <div class="home-container home-header-inner">
        <a href="/" class="home-brand" aria-label="NestForge home">
          <img src="/logo.svg" alt="NestForge" />
          <div class="home-brand-copy">
            <span class="home-brand-name">NestForge</span>
            <span class="home-brand-subtitle">Rust framework docs</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <nav class="home-nav" aria-label="Primary">
          <a href="/getting-started/quick-start/">Quick Start</a>
          <a href="/concepts/architecture/">Architecture</a>
          <a href="/framework/crate-architecture/">Internals</a>
        </nav>

        <div class="home-header-actions">
          <a href="https://github.com/vernonthedev/nestforge" class="home-header-link">GitHub</a>
          <a href="/getting-started/overview/" class="home-header-cta">Open Docs</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="home-container hero-inner">
          <p class="eyebrow">NestForge documentation</p>
          <h1>Build NestForge services without guessing the runtime or the workspace.</h1>
          <p class="hero-copy">
            Documentation for application teams shipping APIs and for contributors working
            inside the framework: installation, CLI workflow, core concepts, transport
            guides, examples, crate architecture, and release process.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a href="/getting-started/quick-start/" class="button button-primary">Quick Start</a>
            <a href="/framework/crate-architecture/" class="button button-secondary">Crate Architecture</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="paths">
        <div class="home-container paths-layout">
          <div class="paths-intro">
            <p class="eyebrow">Choose your lane</p>
            <h2>The docs split cleanly between building on NestForge and evolving NestForge itself.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="paths-stack">
            <a href="/getting-started/overview/" class="path-band">
              <div class="path-band-meta">
                <span class="path-label">Build applications</span>
                <strong>Ship services with the runtime, guides, transports, and examples.</strong>
              </div>
              <p>Start here for installation, request flow, auth, data access, testing, GraphQL, gRPC, WebSockets, and microservices.</p>
            </a>

            <a href="/framework/crate-architecture/" class="path-band path-band-alt">
              <div class="path-band-meta">
                <span class="path-label">Work on the framework</span>
                <strong>Navigate the workspace through crate ownership, API boundaries, and release flow.</strong>
              </div>
              <p>Use this lane for macro internals, workspace structure, contribution rules, framework quality, and release mechanics.</p>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="explore">
        <div class="home-container">
          <div class="explore-head">
            <p class="eyebrow">Jump directly</p>
            <h2>Start from the part of NestForge you need right now.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="explore-layout">
            <a href="/getting-started/quick-start/" class="explore-feature">
              <span class="explore-feature-label">Start here</span>
              <strong>Quick Start</strong>
              <p>Spin up a NestForge project, see the first run path, and move into the docs with context.</p>
            </a>

            <div class="explore-groups">
              <article class="explore-group">
                <span class="explore-group-label">Build</span>
                <a href="/getting-started/installation/">Installation</a>
                <a href="/getting-started/cli-workflow/">CLI Workflow</a>
                <a href="/concepts/architecture/">Architecture</a>
                <a href="/guides/testing/">Testing</a>
                <a href="/examples/hello-nestforge/">Example App</a>
              </article>

              <article class="explore-group">
                <span class="explore-group-label">Runtime</span>
                <a href="/concepts/request-pipeline/">Request Pipeline</a>
                <a href="/guides/auth-openapi/">Auth and OpenAPI</a>
                <a href="/guides/data-layer/">Data Layer</a>
                <a href="/transports/graphql/">GraphQL</a>
                <a href="/transports/grpc/">gRPC</a>
                <a href="/transports/websockets/">WebSockets</a>
                <a href="/transports/microservices/">Microservices</a>
              </article>

              <article class="explore-group">
                <span class="explore-group-label">Framework</span>
                <a href="/framework/workspace-structure/">Workspace Structure</a>
                <a href="/framework/crate-architecture/">Crate Architecture</a>
                <a href="/framework/public-api-surface/">Public API Surface</a>
                <a href="/framework/macro-routing-internals/">Macro Internals</a>
                <a href="/framework/contributing/">Contributing</a>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
